1
00:01:40,729 --> 00:01:42,312
Memories are weird.

2
00:01:43,146 --> 00:01:44,354
They make you laugh.

3
00:01:45,562 --> 00:01:47,771
They make you cry.

4
00:01:50,479 --> 00:01:52,104
Such is my life.

5
00:01:54,229 --> 00:01:55,646
Like the ocean.

6
00:01:57,812 --> 00:01:59,312
What you see on the surface,

7
00:02:00,021 --> 00:02:01,104
is not real.

8
00:02:02,729 --> 00:02:05,479
It conceals dozens of secrets inside.

9
00:02:08,521 --> 00:02:11,062
My job is to clean the ocean,

10
00:02:12,062 --> 00:02:13,396
in a dredging company.

11
00:02:15,604 --> 00:02:17,437
I am trying to find myself

12
00:02:18,146 --> 00:02:19,562
while cleaning the ocean.

13
00:02:21,479 --> 00:02:23,396
I am trying to uncover the secrets

14
00:02:24,187 --> 00:02:27,771
hidden underneath this quiet ocean.

15
00:02:30,354 --> 00:02:31,896
My life is similar to this.

16
00:02:33,437 --> 00:02:35,354
Calm and simple on the surface.

17
00:02:36,271 --> 00:02:40,604
But dark, chaotic,

18
00:02:41,896 --> 00:02:43,104
and complicated on the inside.

19
00:03:35,104 --> 00:03:35,937
Ronnie.

20
00:03:36,354 --> 00:03:37,437
Have you guys reached there?

21
00:03:37,687 --> 00:03:38,646
Where is Tara?

22
00:03:38,854 --> 00:03:39,729
Tara!

23
00:03:45,854 --> 00:03:48,021
Martin. We've just finished the job.

24
00:03:48,396 --> 00:03:49,854
We don't have enough oxygen.

25
00:03:50,062 --> 00:03:51,604
Tara, the Navy is already on the spot.

26
00:03:51,687 --> 00:03:52,896
You just have to assist them.

27
00:03:53,104 --> 00:03:55,396
And report to Captain Aman Sharma
for briefing.

28
00:03:55,479 --> 00:03:56,729
Okay? Thank you.

29
00:03:57,146 --> 00:03:58,021
Martin!

30
00:03:58,187 --> 00:03:59,062
Martin!

31
00:04:02,479 --> 00:04:03,729
This is Tara Salgoankar.

32
00:04:03,812 --> 00:04:04,896
CO of Maria Sea.

33
00:04:04,979 --> 00:04:05,854
Do you copy?

34
00:04:06,354 --> 00:04:08,354
Hi, this is Captain Sharma.
You came right on time.

35
00:04:10,896 --> 00:04:12,062
How can we help, Captain?

36
00:04:12,146 --> 00:04:12,979
There was a blast.

37
00:04:13,062 --> 00:04:14,687
I need you to dive in with your men,

38
00:04:14,812 --> 00:04:16,479
and gather the remains
of the dead crew members.

39
00:04:16,979 --> 00:04:18,062
Of course.

40
00:04:18,854 --> 00:04:20,521
Copy that. Over and out.

41
00:04:22,979 --> 00:04:24,437
I know this is your first time.

42
00:04:24,729 --> 00:04:26,271
But you'll be fine, okay?

43
00:04:40,854 --> 00:04:43,104
As you all just saw,
there was a blast in the hull.

44
00:04:43,187 --> 00:04:44,771
And we're assigned
to excavate the remains

45
00:04:44,854 --> 00:04:46,229
of the dead sailors from the sea.

46
00:04:46,312 --> 00:04:48,021
Look, we do not have enough oxygen

47
00:04:48,104 --> 00:04:49,854
or light here to be negligent.

48
00:04:49,937 --> 00:04:51,271
So we're going to be intelligent,

49
00:04:51,354 --> 00:04:53,104
resourceful, and fast.

50
00:04:53,271 --> 00:04:55,521
And I really need you guys
to follow my lead.

51
00:04:55,854 --> 00:04:58,104
Now, does any one of you
have a cold or congestion?

52
00:04:58,187 --> 00:04:59,021
-No.
-No.

53
00:04:59,104 --> 00:05:01,687
-Is any one of you… drunk?
-No.

54
00:05:02,021 --> 00:05:02,937
-No.
-No!

55
00:05:03,021 --> 00:05:05,271
Great.
You guys already know the rules.

56
00:05:05,354 --> 00:05:07,354
Just follow my instructions
at all times.

57
00:05:07,437 --> 00:05:08,396
Do not panic.

58
00:05:08,521 --> 00:05:11,062
And lastly, don't forget to breathe.

59
00:08:49,354 --> 00:08:50,312
Another one…

60
00:08:51,062 --> 00:08:52,021
down there.

61
00:08:52,104 --> 00:08:53,271
Stuck in the rubble.

62
00:08:53,729 --> 00:08:54,979
We'll need a crane.

63
00:08:55,312 --> 00:08:56,187
Okay.

64
00:08:56,896 --> 00:08:57,979
You notify the Coast Guard

65
00:08:58,062 --> 00:08:59,562
-and send them the coordinates.
-Yes, sir.

66
00:09:14,562 --> 00:09:15,854
I hate you.

67
00:09:19,396 --> 00:09:20,437
I hate you.

68
00:09:22,604 --> 00:09:23,812
I hate you, Tara.

69
00:09:45,854 --> 00:09:47,021
I hate you.

70
00:09:56,771 --> 00:09:58,854
Why don't you quit drinking?

71
00:09:59,562 --> 00:10:00,562
Stop.

72
00:10:00,854 --> 00:10:02,354
-Leave me.
-Look at yourself!

73
00:10:02,521 --> 00:10:03,812
-Look at your condition!
-Shut up!

74
00:10:03,896 --> 00:10:05,271
-Shut up.
-Get out of my life…

75
00:10:05,354 --> 00:10:06,437
I will slap you.

76
00:10:06,521 --> 00:10:09,062
-Do not talk like my father.
-Shut up! Shut up!

77
00:10:09,521 --> 00:10:11,062
-Are you… You don't…
-Shut up!

78
00:10:11,146 --> 00:10:15,062
-care anyway!
-Mom, please. Please don't fight. Stop it!

79
00:10:15,271 --> 00:10:17,187
-Tara. Go back.
-Please, Mom!

80
00:10:17,271 --> 00:10:19,521
-Tara, go back to your room.
-Stop misbehaving with the child.

81
00:10:19,771 --> 00:10:21,646
-Learn to behave.
-I am!

82
00:10:21,729 --> 00:10:23,687
-You be good to me!
-What are you saying?!

83
00:10:25,354 --> 00:10:26,229
Stop!

84
00:10:26,312 --> 00:10:28,396
-I will slap you.
-Let go of my hand!

85
00:10:28,646 --> 00:10:30,062
-Let go!
-Leave my hand!

86
00:10:30,979 --> 00:10:34,021
Are you crazy?
You will die.

87
00:11:03,437 --> 00:11:04,354
Hey…

88
00:11:08,229 --> 00:11:09,187
Tara.

89
00:11:10,187 --> 00:11:11,146
Kabir!

90
00:11:11,646 --> 00:11:12,521
Tara.

91
00:11:14,979 --> 00:11:15,896
Tara!

92
00:11:17,937 --> 00:11:18,812
Are you okay?

93
00:11:23,354 --> 00:11:24,229
Can you breathe?

94
00:11:29,646 --> 00:11:30,687
What the hell is this?

95
00:11:32,271 --> 00:11:33,187
Are you insane?

96
00:11:35,396 --> 00:11:37,187
If I hadn't arrived on time,
you would have joined the dead.

97
00:11:38,312 --> 00:11:39,479
Take her to the medical room.

98
00:12:16,479 --> 00:12:17,396
Tara…

99
00:12:18,271 --> 00:12:20,104
Do you want to get my license canceled?

100
00:12:20,979 --> 00:12:22,396
Your job is only to clean up.

101
00:12:23,146 --> 00:12:24,604
Rescuing is the Navy's job.

102
00:12:25,229 --> 00:12:26,312
Why were you trying to be a hero?

103
00:12:27,687 --> 00:12:28,771
Someone has died.

104
00:12:30,354 --> 00:12:31,687
How can you be so careless?

105
00:12:32,729 --> 00:12:33,604
Call me back.

106
00:12:41,771 --> 00:12:42,896
-You've debriefed them?
-Yes.

107
00:12:42,979 --> 00:12:43,812
-It's done?
-Yes.

108
00:12:43,896 --> 00:12:46,104
-Good.
-Can you tell us about the blast?

109
00:12:46,229 --> 00:12:48,312
The blast happened in a fishing vessel
coming from Italy.

110
00:12:48,521 --> 00:12:49,687
Any casualties?

111
00:12:49,896 --> 00:12:51,729
Unfortunately,
we lost five crew members.

112
00:12:51,812 --> 00:12:53,812
Some minor casualties
and minor injuries.

113
00:12:54,396 --> 00:12:56,146
But the Navy has rescued the others.

114
00:12:56,437 --> 00:12:57,437
No credit to us.

115
00:12:57,812 --> 00:12:58,687
We were there, as well.

116
00:12:59,937 --> 00:13:00,854
Forget it.

117
00:13:06,646 --> 00:13:07,604
Are you okay?

118
00:13:08,312 --> 00:13:09,521
If you are genuinely concerned,

119
00:13:09,771 --> 00:13:11,271
then get your equipment fixed.

120
00:13:11,854 --> 00:13:12,771
Point taken.

121
00:13:13,771 --> 00:13:15,979
But you should have behaved
more responsibly.

122
00:13:16,771 --> 00:13:18,187
If it wasn't for Captain India,

123
00:13:18,396 --> 00:13:19,604
then the matter could have escalated.

124
00:13:20,271 --> 00:13:21,104
Kabir.

125
00:13:21,187 --> 00:13:22,062
Evening, we have an assignment.

126
00:13:22,146 --> 00:13:23,271
-You are coming with me.
-Yes, sir.

127
00:13:23,604 --> 00:13:24,687
There's mass at 7:00 p.m.

128
00:13:24,812 --> 00:13:25,729
You've to attend it.

129
00:13:26,812 --> 00:13:28,062
Another one of your dramas!

130
00:13:28,896 --> 00:13:29,812
That's an order.

131
00:13:31,312 --> 00:13:32,687
The investigation is still going on.

132
00:13:32,771 --> 00:13:34,229
As soon as we get the final reports,

133
00:13:34,312 --> 00:13:36,062
the Navy will release
an official statement

134
00:13:36,146 --> 00:13:37,021
very soon.

135
00:13:37,187 --> 00:13:38,396
Excuse me. Thank you.

136
00:13:40,979 --> 00:13:41,896
Hello, Captain.

137
00:13:42,604 --> 00:13:44,812
Martin. From Martin's Dredging.

138
00:13:45,312 --> 00:13:46,562
Hi. Captain Aman Sharma.

139
00:13:47,187 --> 00:13:50,062
I just wanted to thank you
for saving my mermaid.

140
00:13:51,271 --> 00:13:52,146
Tara.

141
00:13:52,521 --> 00:13:53,396
Oh.

142
00:13:53,979 --> 00:13:55,229
I've heard a lot about you.

143
00:13:56,104 --> 00:13:57,062
Gold medalist.

144
00:13:57,562 --> 00:13:59,312
More than 100 successful missions.

145
00:14:00,354 --> 00:14:01,229
Thank you.

146
00:14:01,896 --> 00:14:06,354
But the Navy's salary
doesn't justify your skills.

147
00:14:08,646 --> 00:14:10,354
Ever thought of joining a private firm?

148
00:14:10,771 --> 00:14:12,229
I never really thought about it.

149
00:14:15,271 --> 00:14:16,271
Just in case.

150
00:14:50,896 --> 00:14:51,771
Hey.

151
00:14:52,437 --> 00:14:54,062
Hey, Captain.

152
00:14:55,229 --> 00:14:56,104
How are you now?

153
00:14:56,271 --> 00:14:57,229
I am good.

154
00:14:58,187 --> 00:14:59,062
Good.

155
00:15:00,604 --> 00:15:01,937
You shouldn't be drinking so much.

156
00:15:03,854 --> 00:15:06,771
And you shouldn't be yelling
at people without a reason.

157
00:15:07,562 --> 00:15:08,729
It hurts.

158
00:15:10,312 --> 00:15:11,229
David.

159
00:15:11,979 --> 00:15:13,229
Get me more, please.

160
00:15:13,396 --> 00:15:14,604
-Sure.
-Thanks.

161
00:15:18,521 --> 00:15:19,437
Can I sit?

162
00:15:20,312 --> 00:15:21,312
The seat's empty.

163
00:15:22,854 --> 00:15:23,979
At your own risk.

164
00:15:30,812 --> 00:15:31,729
To the fallen.

165
00:15:33,229 --> 00:15:34,187
To the fallen.

166
00:15:41,729 --> 00:15:42,604
I am sorry.

167
00:15:44,062 --> 00:15:44,937
Why?

168
00:15:45,021 --> 00:15:48,312
I shouldn't have misbehaved publicly.

169
00:15:50,187 --> 00:15:52,354
You mean if you were alone,
it was okay.

170
00:15:52,979 --> 00:15:54,021
It's not what I meant to say…

171
00:15:54,104 --> 00:15:55,479
And what if you are in bed,

172
00:15:56,729 --> 00:15:58,562
and she really wants it?

173
00:15:59,937 --> 00:16:00,979
Are you flirting with me?

174
00:16:01,937 --> 00:16:02,979
What do you think?

175
00:16:03,562 --> 00:16:04,437
Here you go.

176
00:16:05,104 --> 00:16:06,562
Hi, Captain.

177
00:16:06,687 --> 00:16:07,646
-Hi.
-How are you, man?

178
00:16:08,979 --> 00:16:09,854
David.

179
00:16:10,062 --> 00:16:11,271
You know our Captain

180
00:16:11,354 --> 00:16:12,812
is such a good boy,

181
00:16:13,271 --> 00:16:15,229
that he won't even spank a girl
in bed.

182
00:16:15,312 --> 00:16:17,187
-Why not?
-No, I was…

183
00:16:17,437 --> 00:16:18,771
You're disgusting!

184
00:16:18,937 --> 00:16:19,937
Sorry, Father.

185
00:16:20,771 --> 00:16:21,729
What are you doing?

186
00:16:22,937 --> 00:16:23,979
Can we go someplace else?

187
00:16:24,146 --> 00:16:25,062
Where?

188
00:16:25,604 --> 00:16:27,396
Somewhere away from this boring mass.

189
00:16:29,562 --> 00:16:30,729
-Are you…
-Come.

190
00:16:31,271 --> 00:16:32,146
Where?

191
00:16:32,229 --> 00:16:33,437
Come on. I'll tell you.

192
00:16:40,812 --> 00:16:41,729
What?

193
00:16:43,854 --> 00:16:44,937
Aren't you scared?

194
00:16:45,521 --> 00:16:47,479
Like to… live with the dead.

195
00:16:50,354 --> 00:16:52,062
People who are alive scare me,

196
00:16:52,979 --> 00:16:54,104
not the dead.

197
00:16:55,354 --> 00:16:56,354
But still.

198
00:16:57,396 --> 00:16:59,979
A girl like you… in this profession?

199
00:17:02,562 --> 00:17:03,479
Because…

200
00:17:04,396 --> 00:17:05,771
I am good at it.

201
00:17:07,604 --> 00:17:08,604
Martin…

202
00:17:08,729 --> 00:17:10,812
I mean, Martin doesn't have
a sound track record.

203
00:17:13,312 --> 00:17:16,812
Who cares how Martin is
as long as he pays well

204
00:17:17,104 --> 00:17:18,271
and on time!

205
00:17:20,729 --> 00:17:22,146
Enough about me, Captain.

206
00:17:23,021 --> 00:17:24,187
Tell me something about yourself.

207
00:17:25,771 --> 00:17:27,729
First of all, stop calling me Captain.
My name is Aman.

208
00:17:31,271 --> 00:17:32,646
There isn't much to tell.

209
00:17:33,729 --> 00:17:36,646
My great-grandfather was from Goa.

210
00:17:36,729 --> 00:17:39,312
He settled down here with
a Portuguese sailor.

211
00:17:41,021 --> 00:17:41,896
He settled down here.

212
00:17:42,729 --> 00:17:43,687
I was born here.

213
00:17:45,062 --> 00:17:46,521
I visit India sometimes.

214
00:17:47,687 --> 00:17:49,937
Nothing else has happened
that's worth mentioning.

215
00:17:53,729 --> 00:17:55,729
Nothing special…

216
00:17:56,187 --> 00:17:57,854
An entire ship drowned.

217
00:17:58,104 --> 00:17:59,979
You should give some kind
of credit to life.

218
00:18:01,021 --> 00:18:03,687
Not many witness such an event.

219
00:18:05,312 --> 00:18:06,646
Sorry, I didn't know

220
00:18:07,021 --> 00:18:08,479
we're counting traumatic, as well.

221
00:18:10,354 --> 00:18:12,396
Life consists of everything.

222
00:18:14,687 --> 00:18:17,146
Little water, little sand.

223
00:18:19,104 --> 00:18:20,896
Some clouds, some soil.

224
00:18:21,854 --> 00:18:24,354
The rains, the high tides.

225
00:18:27,021 --> 00:18:28,021
A bit of love.

226
00:18:31,979 --> 00:18:33,104
A bit of chaos.

227
00:18:36,187 --> 00:18:38,187
Nice. That was really good.

228
00:18:38,979 --> 00:18:39,854
You wrote it?

229
00:18:42,896 --> 00:18:44,104
My dad wrote it.

230
00:18:45,437 --> 00:18:46,312
He's a writer?

231
00:18:48,229 --> 00:18:50,146
No. He's retired.

232
00:18:51,479 --> 00:18:52,771
He does everything he wants to.

233
00:18:53,646 --> 00:18:54,521
And mom?

234
00:18:56,729 --> 00:18:57,604
Dead.

235
00:19:01,229 --> 00:19:02,104
I am really sorry.

236
00:19:03,979 --> 00:19:04,937
It's okay.

237
00:19:05,687 --> 00:19:08,062
It was… a long time ago.

238
00:19:09,646 --> 00:19:10,729
Are you feeling cold?

239
00:19:30,729 --> 00:19:31,687
I am okay.

240
00:19:32,187 --> 00:19:33,812
Leave me. I am fine.

241
00:19:33,896 --> 00:19:34,771
Sorry.

242
00:19:39,312 --> 00:19:40,229
Are you okay?

243
00:19:45,187 --> 00:19:46,062
Wow!

244
00:19:47,021 --> 00:19:48,271
So many aquariums.

245
00:19:50,896 --> 00:19:51,812
It's illegal.

246
00:19:51,896 --> 00:19:53,187
Is this your side business?

247
00:19:53,271 --> 00:19:54,146
Shut up.

248
00:19:54,896 --> 00:19:56,312
I love aquariums.

249
00:19:57,312 --> 00:19:58,312
They help me…

250
00:19:59,187 --> 00:20:00,271
relax.

251
00:20:03,729 --> 00:20:05,521
Grandma doesn't like that I drink.

252
00:20:06,771 --> 00:20:08,354
That's why…

253
00:20:10,854 --> 00:20:11,937
I keep a water bottle…

254
00:20:13,521 --> 00:20:14,396
filled with vodka.

255
00:20:25,021 --> 00:20:25,979
Cheers.

256
00:20:26,396 --> 00:20:27,396
Cheers.

257
00:20:34,687 --> 00:20:35,604
Oh, pickle.

258
00:20:36,562 --> 00:20:37,562
Can I have some, please?

259
00:20:38,562 --> 00:20:39,521
-No.
-Only a little, please?

260
00:20:40,521 --> 00:20:41,896
We just put it to dry yesterday.

261
00:20:42,312 --> 00:20:45,229
If you open it, it will be
ruined. And grandma will be…

262
00:20:53,104 --> 00:20:54,312
Make yourself at home.

263
00:20:54,604 --> 00:20:55,479
Okay.

264
00:20:55,646 --> 00:20:56,854
I'll be right back.

265
00:21:58,062 --> 00:21:58,937
Captain,

266
00:22:00,229 --> 00:22:01,271
ready to sail?

267
00:22:13,146 --> 00:22:14,104
What are you doing?

268
00:22:15,312 --> 00:22:16,729
What do you think?

269
00:22:17,187 --> 00:22:18,562
That you are drunk?

270
00:22:20,146 --> 00:22:21,021
So…

271
00:22:23,062 --> 00:22:24,437
don't you want this?

272
00:22:25,271 --> 00:22:26,229
Captain.

273
00:22:32,354 --> 00:22:33,229
Tara?

274
00:22:45,229 --> 00:22:47,354
What will you do
with all these pickles?

275
00:22:47,604 --> 00:22:49,521
Have you been selling them?

276
00:22:50,021 --> 00:22:52,437
No. Only four of these are for me.

277
00:22:53,062 --> 00:22:56,604
The rest are for Monu,
Bittu, Nanu and Bhoomi.

278
00:22:57,479 --> 00:22:59,854
Why don't we buy ready-made
pickles like the rest?

279
00:23:00,146 --> 00:23:01,646
It's not all that bad.

280
00:23:01,854 --> 00:23:04,271
Oh, no… readymade pickle!

281
00:23:05,646 --> 00:23:09,479
I wonder what ingredients
they use to make it quickly.

282
00:23:10,146 --> 00:23:12,896
Pickle is the sweet fruit of patience.

283
00:23:13,271 --> 00:23:14,187
Hard work.

284
00:23:14,479 --> 00:23:15,354
Wait.

285
00:23:15,646 --> 00:23:18,771
Lots of spices and sea salt.

286
00:23:18,979 --> 00:23:22,021
The saying goes,
"Whoever's body the sea salt touches,

287
00:23:22,187 --> 00:23:23,687
is blessed with a long life."

288
00:23:24,229 --> 00:23:25,271
Take me for instance.

289
00:23:25,812 --> 00:23:28,604
I'll be turning 72 soon.

290
00:23:28,979 --> 00:23:30,396
No! Not at all!

291
00:23:31,646 --> 00:23:33,812
Do you mean you were a diver like me?

292
00:23:33,979 --> 00:23:35,062
Absolutely.

293
00:23:35,521 --> 00:23:37,646
As a kid, I would dive right
into the ocean.

294
00:23:37,896 --> 00:23:40,979
I was the best swimmer in my village.

295
00:23:42,479 --> 00:23:43,521
Mom, can I taste it?

296
00:23:43,979 --> 00:23:44,854
Go ahead.

297
00:23:49,229 --> 00:23:51,104
Did you cover it with sugar or something?

298
00:23:51,312 --> 00:23:52,521
-Tastes weird.
-Why will I add sugar?!

299
00:23:53,104 --> 00:23:54,104
Check, dear.

300
00:23:57,062 --> 00:23:58,146
It's so nice.

301
00:23:58,604 --> 00:23:59,521
Unnecessarily…

302
00:24:00,562 --> 00:24:02,646
And who do you think
you take after?

303
00:24:03,604 --> 00:24:05,521
Your father is an earth lover.

304
00:24:05,604 --> 00:24:06,771
Like your grandpa.

305
00:24:07,646 --> 00:24:10,687
But we Salgoankar women
are daughters of the ocean.

306
00:24:11,187 --> 00:24:13,104
God. I am late.

307
00:24:13,187 --> 00:24:14,187
I've to get to work.

308
00:24:14,562 --> 00:24:16,271
Why don't you quit this job?

309
00:24:16,729 --> 00:24:18,646
I am the daughter of the ocean.
Remember?

310
00:24:22,646 --> 00:24:24,104
But you've to live on earth.

311
00:24:24,437 --> 00:24:25,729
You will have to return.

312
00:24:26,146 --> 00:24:30,021
I will and I will make
the best pickle like you.

313
00:24:31,021 --> 00:24:32,312
But not now.

314
00:24:32,437 --> 00:24:34,021
-Understood!
-I'm having another one.

315
00:24:34,104 --> 00:24:35,312
It's amazing.

316
00:24:35,521 --> 00:24:36,771
-Bye.
-Bye.

317
00:24:53,062 --> 00:24:54,229
-Good morning, Tara.
-Good morning.

318
00:24:54,312 --> 00:24:55,396
-Good morning, David.
-Good morning.

319
00:24:55,479 --> 00:24:57,146
Heard about the incident.
How are you?

320
00:24:57,229 --> 00:24:58,646
I am good now.
Thanks.

321
00:25:08,146 --> 00:25:08,979
So…

322
00:25:09,562 --> 00:25:10,479
So, what?

323
00:25:11,146 --> 00:25:12,021
How was your date?

324
00:25:16,187 --> 00:25:17,312
We're going for the office picnic.

325
00:25:19,854 --> 00:25:20,937
I can't come.

326
00:25:21,771 --> 00:25:23,146
But it's compulsory.

327
00:25:23,646 --> 00:25:24,604
Says who?

328
00:25:25,396 --> 00:25:26,271
I did.

329
00:25:27,062 --> 00:25:28,646
This is an office, not a school.

330
00:25:29,312 --> 00:25:31,896
And anyway,
I've to clean my fish tank.

331
00:25:32,396 --> 00:25:33,479
I can't come.

332
00:25:34,521 --> 00:25:36,271
Clean your fish tank on Sunday.

333
00:25:36,771 --> 00:25:37,937
The picnic is on Saturday.

334
00:25:38,687 --> 00:25:39,729
And you are coming.

335
00:25:40,187 --> 00:25:41,229
We've already made the booking.

336
00:25:41,812 --> 00:25:43,146
I've five and not one.

337
00:25:43,437 --> 00:25:44,896
The largest tank is ten feet tall.

338
00:25:45,312 --> 00:25:46,271
Takes time.

339
00:25:47,521 --> 00:25:50,562
And if it's too much trouble,
then deduct it from my salary.

340
00:25:51,437 --> 00:25:52,937
I am not running a corner store,

341
00:25:54,104 --> 00:25:55,187
to deduct your salary.

342
00:25:55,771 --> 00:25:56,812
Don't come if you don't want to.

343
00:25:57,604 --> 00:25:59,812
"Deduct my salary!"
That's all I had to hear.

344
00:26:30,979 --> 00:26:31,854
-Hi.
-Hi.

345
00:26:31,937 --> 00:26:33,062
I've come to see Tara.

346
00:26:33,437 --> 00:26:34,437
I'll call her.

347
00:26:40,104 --> 00:26:41,187
What exactly happened last night

348
00:26:41,396 --> 00:26:43,479
that the Navy landed up
on our doorstep in the morning?

349
00:26:45,646 --> 00:26:48,437
Shit! Damn it!

350
00:26:50,771 --> 00:26:51,896
-Hey.
-Hi.

351
00:26:52,437 --> 00:26:54,479
What are you doing here?

352
00:26:55,604 --> 00:26:56,604
This is for you.

353
00:26:57,271 --> 00:26:58,354
I hate flowers.

354
00:26:58,437 --> 00:26:59,562
I love flowers.

355
00:27:07,062 --> 00:27:08,687
This is my workplace, Aman.

356
00:27:09,729 --> 00:27:11,604
You passed out last night
before giving your number.

357
00:27:12,479 --> 00:27:14,896
I could have gone to your house
or here.

358
00:27:15,646 --> 00:27:17,979
And anyway, I feel it's too soon
to meet your family, right?

359
00:27:20,021 --> 00:27:20,854
What say?

360
00:27:20,937 --> 00:27:21,896
Can we continue last night's date?

361
00:27:23,187 --> 00:27:24,937
-You know, I…
-Forget it.

362
00:27:25,312 --> 00:27:26,937
Your receptionist seems nice.

363
00:27:27,021 --> 00:27:28,187
I'll… ask her.

364
00:27:28,604 --> 00:27:30,062
-You dog!
-What…

365
00:27:39,771 --> 00:27:44,021
The world's so cruel

366
00:27:44,396 --> 00:27:48,604
You are like the soother in my life

367
00:27:49,146 --> 00:27:50,437
When we met

368
00:27:50,521 --> 00:27:53,729
I felt closer to God

369
00:27:53,854 --> 00:27:57,187
Seems like I am in love

370
00:27:57,521 --> 00:28:01,771
My heart goes out to you, beloved

371
00:28:02,062 --> 00:28:05,354
Can't live without you

372
00:28:05,646 --> 00:28:10,271
I've renounced the world in your love

373
00:28:10,354 --> 00:28:14,479
I've renounced the world in your love

374
00:28:14,937 --> 00:28:18,479
I've become a wanderer

375
00:28:18,562 --> 00:28:22,937
My heart goes out to you, beloved

376
00:28:23,229 --> 00:28:26,562
Can't live without you

377
00:28:26,854 --> 00:28:30,979
I've renounced the world in your love

378
00:28:31,396 --> 00:28:38,312
I've become a wanderer

379
00:28:56,312 --> 00:29:00,521
Can't see anyone beyond you

380
00:29:00,771 --> 00:29:05,396
All your wishes have been answered

381
00:29:05,771 --> 00:29:09,979
You are the one I see

382
00:29:10,229 --> 00:29:15,021
You dwell inside me, beloved

383
00:29:15,479 --> 00:29:17,771
My days and nights

384
00:29:17,854 --> 00:29:20,062
Are spent talking about you

385
00:29:20,146 --> 00:29:22,437
With you, I want to be

386
00:29:22,562 --> 00:29:26,729
Forever and ever

387
00:29:27,104 --> 00:29:29,396
-Where are we going?
-I have a surprise for you.

388
00:29:31,437 --> 00:29:34,812
-Can't live without you
-Come.

389
00:29:35,021 --> 00:29:37,979
I've renounced the world…

390
00:29:38,062 --> 00:29:39,396
Come, I want to show you something.

391
00:29:39,521 --> 00:29:41,104
Come. It's a surprise.

392
00:29:41,354 --> 00:29:42,229
Look.

393
00:29:43,896 --> 00:29:45,937
Does the mermaid look familiar?

394
00:29:50,812 --> 00:29:51,979
It's a tribute to you.

395
00:30:28,854 --> 00:30:29,771
Tara.

396
00:30:55,896 --> 00:30:56,812
Tara.

397
00:30:56,979 --> 00:30:57,896
Tara!

398
00:30:58,062 --> 00:30:58,896
Tara!

399
00:31:01,396 --> 00:31:02,812
Calm down.

400
00:31:03,104 --> 00:31:04,562
It's okay.

401
00:31:04,687 --> 00:31:06,562
It's okay. It's okay…

402
00:31:11,896 --> 00:31:12,937
Thank you so much, sir.

403
00:31:13,479 --> 00:31:15,104
-I am really sorry.
-Please be careful.

404
00:31:15,271 --> 00:31:16,271
Yeah, fine.

405
00:31:31,687 --> 00:31:32,646
What drama was that?

406
00:31:34,104 --> 00:31:35,479
-I was doing a drama?
-Was it me then?

407
00:31:36,937 --> 00:31:37,812
What is this?

408
00:31:39,271 --> 00:31:41,437
Look, I am really sorry about this.

409
00:31:44,146 --> 00:31:45,896
But why did you have to do all this?

410
00:31:46,479 --> 00:31:47,729
And was this your surprise?

411
00:31:48,354 --> 00:31:49,812
A ship that was littered
with dead bodies?

412
00:31:49,896 --> 00:31:50,979
You were there.

413
00:31:51,062 --> 00:31:53,146
I just wanted
to do something nice for you, Tara.

414
00:31:54,229 --> 00:31:55,771
By recreating a tragedy?

415
00:31:56,729 --> 00:31:58,937
Wow. Genius.

416
00:32:00,229 --> 00:32:01,146
It's my fault…

417
00:32:03,646 --> 00:32:05,354
that I loved a drama queen like you!

418
00:32:07,187 --> 00:32:08,479
Do you even know…

419
00:32:37,187 --> 00:32:38,062
Ramesh.

420
00:32:39,021 --> 00:32:39,937
Look.

421
00:32:40,771 --> 00:32:43,271
Your daughter made us proud.

422
00:32:48,437 --> 00:32:49,396
Come on, Mom.

423
00:32:49,562 --> 00:32:51,812
Don't start this in the morning.

424
00:32:52,229 --> 00:32:54,479
People are saying
Tara was completely out of control.

425
00:32:54,979 --> 00:32:56,479
Like she was possessed.

426
00:32:56,562 --> 00:32:57,521
Mom…

427
00:32:58,062 --> 00:33:00,062
we are gearing up to go on Mars.

428
00:33:00,479 --> 00:33:02,271
And you are still stuck
on ghosts and spirits.

429
00:33:02,354 --> 00:33:04,437
Everyone in the family knows.

430
00:33:04,562 --> 00:33:05,812
They are all talking about it.

431
00:33:06,146 --> 00:33:08,312
Like mother like daughter is
what they are all saying.

432
00:33:09,229 --> 00:33:10,271
Not your daughter.

433
00:33:11,854 --> 00:33:13,771
If you can't stand me, then I'll leave.

434
00:33:16,104 --> 00:33:17,229
Like Mom did.

435
00:33:18,062 --> 00:33:20,312
Then you can take care of your "family."

436
00:33:20,479 --> 00:33:22,812
Forget it.
You know Mom's nature.

437
00:33:23,104 --> 00:33:25,521
See how audacious she is!

438
00:33:25,979 --> 00:33:26,937
Mannerless!

439
00:33:27,104 --> 00:33:28,729
You please calm down, Mom.

440
00:33:28,896 --> 00:33:31,729
I will calm down,
but what about the world?

441
00:33:32,479 --> 00:33:34,396
I didn't do it intentionally, Grandma.

442
00:33:35,062 --> 00:33:36,021
I know.

443
00:33:36,771 --> 00:33:37,896
This is why I kept saying,

444
00:33:38,229 --> 00:33:40,312
stop hanging around dead bodies

445
00:33:40,521 --> 00:33:42,771
and join me or your father.

446
00:33:43,021 --> 00:33:44,854
Now you've brought
some spirit back with you.

447
00:33:45,396 --> 00:33:46,521
I can't deal with this.

448
00:33:46,604 --> 00:33:47,437
Tara.

449
00:33:47,521 --> 00:33:48,396
Tara.

450
00:33:52,354 --> 00:33:53,396
What is this, Mom?

451
00:33:54,604 --> 00:33:56,854
You say such absurd things.
Think before you speak.

452
00:33:57,521 --> 00:33:59,562
Why did you have
to bring Sukanya into this?

453
00:35:18,604 --> 00:35:19,521
Hey.

454
00:35:20,146 --> 00:35:22,021
Hi.
So, what did you find?

455
00:35:22,146 --> 00:35:23,854
Straight to the point as always.

456
00:35:24,021 --> 00:35:26,979
So, Leslie Fernandes used to work
for the Indian Embassy,

457
00:35:27,062 --> 00:35:28,104
but now he's retired.

458
00:35:28,271 --> 00:35:31,812
And after some digging,
I found a trail to Sicily.

459
00:35:32,396 --> 00:35:34,479
So I am going to go there
and do some more digging,

460
00:35:34,771 --> 00:35:36,396
and let you know what I find there.

461
00:35:36,604 --> 00:35:37,687
But as always,

462
00:35:37,854 --> 00:35:39,062
I am going to need some more cash.

463
00:35:39,271 --> 00:35:40,187
Yeah.

464
00:35:45,937 --> 00:35:46,812
Thank you.

465
00:35:48,312 --> 00:35:49,687
Always a pleasure, Tara.

466
00:36:25,479 --> 00:36:26,312
Hi.

467
00:36:26,646 --> 00:36:27,521
Hey.

468
00:36:27,604 --> 00:36:28,437
Indian?

469
00:36:28,521 --> 00:36:29,896
Wow. Me too.

470
00:36:29,979 --> 00:36:31,104
How can I help you?

471
00:36:31,687 --> 00:36:32,687
Hi, I'm Neil.

472
00:36:34,354 --> 00:36:35,187
Tara.

473
00:36:35,271 --> 00:36:37,146
Actually, I needed a pond cleaned.

474
00:36:38,479 --> 00:36:40,521
Sorry, we're booked
for the entire month.

475
00:36:40,646 --> 00:36:41,521
I can't help you.

476
00:36:41,729 --> 00:36:42,646
Thanks.

477
00:36:42,937 --> 00:36:44,396
-The entire month?
-Yeah.

478
00:36:44,521 --> 00:36:45,687
Because of the carnival.

479
00:36:45,771 --> 00:36:46,937
It's a busy month.

480
00:36:48,396 --> 00:36:49,479
Please help me out.

481
00:36:49,854 --> 00:36:51,479
In fact, I can pay you extra
if you want.

482
00:36:52,771 --> 00:36:53,854
Is it an emergency?

483
00:36:54,104 --> 00:36:55,146
A big emergency.

484
00:36:55,354 --> 00:36:56,562
It's an unattended pond.

485
00:36:56,687 --> 00:36:57,729
If anyone falls in it,

486
00:36:57,812 --> 00:36:58,771
it can be an emergency.

487
00:36:59,229 --> 00:37:00,937
-Very funny.
-It's a life risk.

488
00:37:01,437 --> 00:37:03,771
Call me when someone falls in it, alright?

489
00:37:03,854 --> 00:37:05,437
Thank you. Please.
I am busy.

490
00:37:05,854 --> 00:37:09,229
Tara, I am planning to throw
the grandest party in Malta's history.

491
00:37:09,687 --> 00:37:11,437
But a dirty pond
will make it impossible.

492
00:37:11,729 --> 00:37:12,854
My reputation is at stake.

493
00:37:13,146 --> 00:37:14,896
-A party!
-It's not an ordinary party.

494
00:37:15,812 --> 00:37:16,896
The grandest party.

495
00:37:17,812 --> 00:37:18,687
Ever!

496
00:37:18,771 --> 00:37:20,062
Please give me your address.

497
00:37:20,146 --> 00:37:21,187
-Yeah, sure.
-Yeah.

498
00:37:21,979 --> 00:37:23,396
-Yeah.
-I'll see you then.

499
00:37:24,104 --> 00:37:27,646
You? You don't have to come.
You can send any diver.

500
00:37:27,771 --> 00:37:28,771
I am the diver.

501
00:37:29,604 --> 00:37:30,479
Wow.

502
00:37:48,646 --> 00:37:49,896
Do you know what's happening?

503
00:37:52,562 --> 00:37:53,437
What do you mean?

504
00:37:55,271 --> 00:37:56,687
He's trying to replace you.

505
00:37:59,271 --> 00:38:00,146
Rubbish!

506
00:38:00,562 --> 00:38:02,187
You say such absurd things, Kabir.

507
00:38:03,687 --> 00:38:04,771
Navy boy Aman.

508
00:38:05,479 --> 00:38:06,562
I've heard rumors.

509
00:38:08,104 --> 00:38:10,812
Aman? He hates Martin's Dredging's.

510
00:38:11,729 --> 00:38:14,479
He was telling me to quit.

511
00:38:15,104 --> 00:38:16,604
So that he can take your place.

512
00:38:17,562 --> 00:38:19,021
Why would he quit his job in the Navy

513
00:38:19,687 --> 00:38:21,812
and clean garbage
from the ocean with us?

514
00:38:22,312 --> 00:38:23,812
Does not make sense.

515
00:38:25,312 --> 00:38:26,729
Money, Babu bhaiyya, money!

516
00:38:27,396 --> 00:38:28,562
It's a curse!

517
00:38:54,521 --> 00:38:57,062
Tara, are you really leaving?

518
00:38:58,687 --> 00:39:00,979
Yes. I'll be back in a couple of days.

519
00:39:02,521 --> 00:39:05,896
Don't take offense
to what Mom said, please.

520
00:39:10,229 --> 00:39:14,479
Keep feeding my fishes, please.

521
00:39:14,854 --> 00:39:15,771
Okay.

522
00:39:29,521 --> 00:39:30,521
What do you want, Aman?

523
00:39:30,729 --> 00:39:31,687
Forgiveness.

524
00:39:33,062 --> 00:39:34,229
I acted immaturely.

525
00:39:35,396 --> 00:39:37,646
It's okay. It's all in the past.

526
00:39:38,312 --> 00:39:39,354
You are the best.

527
00:39:40,604 --> 00:39:41,687
I have something to tell you.

528
00:39:41,771 --> 00:39:42,729
You are quitting the Navy.

529
00:39:43,437 --> 00:39:44,312
How do you know?

530
00:39:45,729 --> 00:39:46,854
That Martin…

531
00:39:47,354 --> 00:39:48,562
I told him to keep it a secret.

532
00:39:50,021 --> 00:39:51,312
I wanted to surprise you.

533
00:39:51,604 --> 00:39:54,021
Listen, I don't want
any more surprises, okay?

534
00:39:54,312 --> 00:39:56,021
Your surprises give me nightmares.

535
00:39:56,396 --> 00:39:57,896
I thought you would be happy to know.

536
00:39:58,021 --> 00:40:00,312
Come on, stop pretending.

537
00:40:00,604 --> 00:40:02,896
As soon as you found out I was not fit,
you came to take my place.

538
00:40:03,104 --> 00:40:04,562
You didn't even like Martin.

539
00:40:04,646 --> 00:40:05,854
You were telling me to quit.

540
00:40:05,979 --> 00:40:06,896
So what changed now?

541
00:40:07,187 --> 00:40:09,187
Tara, calm down.

542
00:40:09,437 --> 00:40:10,979
I've no interest in taking your place.

543
00:40:11,062 --> 00:40:13,646
Martin told me to do it.
He needed help.

544
00:40:13,729 --> 00:40:14,604
He begged me.

545
00:40:14,896 --> 00:40:16,271
Kabir heard something else.

546
00:40:16,396 --> 00:40:18,396
You trust someone
else's word over mine.

547
00:40:19,354 --> 00:40:21,187
Listen, I've got to go.

548
00:40:21,271 --> 00:40:22,187
Tara.

549
00:40:22,479 --> 00:40:23,396
Tara.

550
00:41:02,021 --> 00:41:02,896
Yes?

551
00:41:09,104 --> 00:41:10,312
Martin's Dredging.

552
00:41:12,271 --> 00:41:13,479
Oh, yes, Neil told me about it.

553
00:41:13,896 --> 00:41:14,771
Please, come in.

554
00:41:16,979 --> 00:41:18,437
Neil will be with you in a minute.

555
00:41:19,354 --> 00:41:20,687
Please, make yourself at home.

556
00:41:21,979 --> 00:41:22,937
Bathroom.

557
00:41:23,812 --> 00:41:24,937
Just down there, to the left.

558
00:41:25,396 --> 00:41:26,271
Thanks.

559
