Show him around.

1113
01:17:11,604 --> 01:17:12,562
Please.

1114
01:17:13,437 --> 01:17:14,479
Back to work.

1115
01:17:15,354 --> 01:17:17,396
So… this is your cabin.

1116
01:17:18,771 --> 01:17:20,354
Your chair and desk.

1117
01:17:21,312 --> 01:17:22,271
Oh, nice.

1118
01:17:23,271 --> 01:17:24,771
Let me know if you need anything else.

1119
01:17:25,062 --> 01:17:25,937
Sure.

1120
01:17:32,521 --> 01:17:33,604
This belongs to Tara.

1121
01:18:13,437 --> 01:18:14,354
Come, I'll apply.

1122
01:18:15,312 --> 01:18:16,687
No. I will manage.

1123
01:18:17,021 --> 01:18:17,979
I can see that.

1124
01:18:18,562 --> 01:18:19,437
Give it.

1125
01:18:19,979 --> 01:18:20,854
Cool.

1126
01:19:52,812 --> 01:19:53,687
Kabir.

1127
01:19:54,271 --> 01:19:55,521
Did you have a word with Tara?

1128
01:19:56,271 --> 01:19:57,229
She isn't picking up her phone.

1129
01:19:57,937 --> 01:20:00,062
I spoke to her the day before yesterday.

1130
01:20:00,312 --> 01:20:01,437
She seemed okay to me.

1131
01:20:01,604 --> 01:20:02,729
Anything wrong?

1132
01:20:03,271 --> 01:20:04,646
No, she isn't picking up her phone.

1133
01:20:05,271 --> 01:20:06,771
Where is Martin's guesthouse?

1134
01:20:08,271 --> 01:20:09,937
You don't need to worry.

1135
01:20:10,021 --> 01:20:11,896
She doesn't use her phone much.

1136
01:20:12,604 --> 01:20:13,854
I think she is fine.

1137
01:20:33,187 --> 01:20:34,396
-Is this the one?
-Yeah.

1138
01:20:39,687 --> 01:20:40,646
I would have come inside,

1139
01:20:40,812 --> 01:20:42,396
but I am getting late for my performance.

1140
01:20:42,687 --> 01:20:43,562
It's okay.

1141
01:20:45,979 --> 01:20:47,312
I'll see you there.

1142
01:20:47,937 --> 01:20:48,812
Tara.

1143
01:20:51,937 --> 01:20:53,021
Don't get lost this time.

1144
01:20:53,562 --> 01:20:54,437
Please.

1145
01:20:55,146 --> 01:20:56,146
I'll see you there.

1146
01:21:05,937 --> 01:21:08,396
The last time I saw you,
you were only two years old.

1147
01:21:11,312 --> 01:21:14,854
How are Ramesh and Sukanya?
They didn't come along?

1148
01:21:16,187 --> 01:21:17,229
Dad is fine.

1149
01:21:18,146 --> 01:21:19,021
But…

1150
01:21:20,729 --> 01:21:22,437
mom is no more.

1151
01:21:24,396 --> 01:21:25,354
What?

1152
01:21:25,562 --> 01:21:27,229
She passed away ten years ago.

1153
01:21:28,187 --> 01:21:29,062
How?

1154
01:21:29,562 --> 01:21:30,562
Suicide.

1155
01:21:32,229 --> 01:21:34,187
Oh, God!

1156
01:21:35,771 --> 01:21:36,771
Sorry.

1157
01:21:39,021 --> 01:21:40,104
I am so sorry.

1158
01:21:40,687 --> 01:21:42,479
It must have been terrible
for you and Ramesh.

1159
01:21:43,312 --> 01:21:44,687
I want to ask you something.

1160
01:21:59,812 --> 01:22:01,687
What happened in Goa 30 years ago?

1161
01:22:05,812 --> 01:22:07,104
Whatever it was, just forget it.

1162
01:22:10,937 --> 01:22:11,896
Please, sir.

1163
01:22:12,896 --> 01:22:14,104
I really need to know…

1164
01:22:15,687 --> 01:22:16,979
why she killed herself.

1165
01:22:18,979 --> 01:22:20,271
Are you capable of hearing the truth?

1166
01:22:20,646 --> 01:22:21,687
That's why I am here.

1167
01:22:26,187 --> 01:22:27,687
You are Sukanya's daughter…

1168
01:22:31,146 --> 01:22:32,229
but not Ramesh's.

1169
01:22:34,562 --> 01:22:35,729
What nonsense!

1170
01:22:36,021 --> 01:22:37,479
And what are you even saying?

1171
01:22:38,437 --> 01:22:40,229
How dare you even
say something like this?

1172
01:22:41,604 --> 01:22:42,729
Why did I come here?

1173
01:22:42,937 --> 01:22:44,354
I am leaving.

1174
01:22:45,021 --> 01:22:46,229
After hearing only half the truth?

1175
01:22:48,896 --> 01:22:50,812
Me, Sukanya, and our group,

1176
01:22:52,729 --> 01:22:53,937
we all went to Goa.

1177
01:22:55,229 --> 01:22:57,937
Thinking we might meet George Harrison.

1178
01:22:59,062 --> 01:23:02,771
We went to Goa but no one had
any idea how to meet him.

1179
01:23:03,146 --> 01:23:06,687
For a week we searched every lane,
every alley, and every beach in Goa.

1180
01:23:07,271 --> 01:23:08,396
But we couldn't find Harrison.

1181
01:23:09,354 --> 01:23:10,354
But the next day…

1182
01:23:12,854 --> 01:23:14,604
You think we will find him here?

1183
01:23:14,729 --> 01:23:16,062
I hope we do.

1184
01:23:16,687 --> 01:23:18,187
It'll be really amazing.

1185
01:23:22,021 --> 01:23:23,771
Sukanya, I am telling you.
This is the last party we attend.

1186
01:23:23,979 --> 01:23:25,396
After this, we are heading home.

1187
01:23:37,896 --> 01:23:38,937
-Hey.
-Hey!

1188
01:23:41,354 --> 01:23:42,229
Shall we?

1189
01:23:43,229 --> 01:23:44,229
I have to go.

1190
01:23:44,604 --> 01:23:45,562
Go where?

1191
01:23:46,771 --> 01:23:48,937
Well… actually,

1192
01:23:49,479 --> 01:23:50,771
I am looking for someone.

1193
01:23:50,979 --> 01:23:51,896
Then stay.

1194
01:23:52,687 --> 01:23:56,104
Maybe this is where your search ends.

1195
01:23:58,479 --> 01:23:59,354
Right?

1196
01:24:02,187 --> 01:24:04,437
-Let's stay for a while…
-It's okay.

1197
01:24:04,896 --> 01:24:05,854
You enjoy.

1198
01:24:05,937 --> 01:24:07,062
Wait. Leslie.

1199
01:24:07,479 --> 01:24:10,396
Your boyfriend seems
pretty possessive.

1200
01:24:10,646 --> 01:24:11,771
He's not my boyfriend.

1201
01:24:11,937 --> 01:24:13,604
-Really?
-No.

1202
01:24:13,687 --> 01:24:15,354
Then what are you doing
with him in Goa?

1203
01:24:16,604 --> 01:24:19,646
If I tell you, you will laugh at me.

1204
01:24:19,937 --> 01:24:21,396
Then you must tell me.

1205
01:24:21,771 --> 01:24:23,271
I want to meet George Harrison.

1206
01:24:27,521 --> 01:24:28,771
You're laughing at me.

1207
01:24:30,146 --> 01:24:32,229
-You're laughing at me!
-Sorry. I am sorry.

1208
01:24:32,437 --> 01:24:33,896
You want to meet George Harrison?

1209
01:24:33,979 --> 01:24:35,562
Yeah. Wait!

1210
01:24:35,979 --> 01:24:37,437
You know George Harrison?

1211
01:24:37,687 --> 01:24:38,687
Of course.

1212
01:24:38,896 --> 01:24:41,062
-Oh, my…
-Look at this guitar. George Harrison.

1213
01:24:41,896 --> 01:24:43,479
Oh, my God.

1214
01:24:44,562 --> 01:24:45,521
Can I touch it?

1215
01:24:45,604 --> 01:24:46,812
You can play it.

1216
01:24:49,229 --> 01:24:51,187
-Here.
-Okay.

1217
01:24:51,729 --> 01:24:52,979
Be careful with this.

1218
01:24:53,562 --> 01:24:55,562
KAILASH

1219
01:24:57,687 --> 01:24:58,854
KAILASH

1220
01:25:06,479 --> 01:25:07,771
What is your name?

1221
01:25:08,646 --> 01:25:09,646
Sukanya.

1222
01:25:10,021 --> 01:25:11,021
I am Kailash.

1223
01:25:14,021 --> 01:25:15,021
Hi, Kailash.

1224
01:25:16,021 --> 01:25:18,854
After coming back from Goa,
Ramesh and Sukanya got married.

1225
01:25:23,562 --> 01:25:24,646
This can't be true.

1226
01:25:26,521 --> 01:25:27,562
You are lying.

1227
01:25:29,021 --> 01:25:31,562
Because my mom chose my dad,
and not you.

1228
01:25:32,229 --> 01:25:33,354
I read in the diary.

1229
01:25:33,646 --> 01:25:34,771
You are just lying.

1230
01:25:35,271 --> 01:25:36,312
You are lying, right?

1231
01:25:36,396 --> 01:25:37,396
Yes, you are.

1232
01:25:38,521 --> 01:25:40,229
I don't know why I came here!

1233
01:25:49,896 --> 01:25:52,354
Like a dream she was

1234
01:25:53,312 --> 01:25:56,146
A broken star

1235
01:25:56,729 --> 01:25:59,187
-Where do I look for her now?
-30 years ago, when Arlo lived in Goa,

1236
01:25:59,271 --> 01:26:01,187
he hosted George Harrison.

1237
01:26:03,646 --> 01:26:06,187
It was the heart's wish

1238
01:26:07,229 --> 01:26:09,979
To let it go

1239
01:26:10,937 --> 01:26:16,771
I wonder when the sky turned dark?

1240
01:26:17,437 --> 01:26:20,437
What I got

1241
01:26:20,937 --> 01:26:23,771
Isn't what I had imagined

1242
01:26:24,312 --> 01:26:27,104
In exchange for my dreams

1243
01:26:27,812 --> 01:26:30,812
All I got was deceit

1244
01:26:31,312 --> 01:26:37,729
Like a shadow in these empty hands

1245
01:26:38,229 --> 01:26:41,062
What we got

1246
01:26:41,687 --> 01:26:44,146
Isn't what we had imagined

1247
01:26:45,104 --> 01:26:47,896
On a blank paper

1248
01:26:48,604 --> 01:26:51,521
I painted your smile

1249
01:26:52,229 --> 01:26:54,812
Carried away by the wind

1250
01:26:58,854 --> 01:27:01,812
Couldn't complete this story

1251
01:27:02,646 --> 01:27:05,479
That I was once narrating

1252
01:27:06,104 --> 01:27:12,146
Which was once our story

1253
01:27:12,771 --> 01:27:15,812
What I got

1254
01:27:16,187 --> 01:27:19,062
Isn't what I had imagined

1255
01:27:19,604 --> 01:27:22,646
In exchange for my dreams

1256
