-Isn't what we had imagined
-Isn't what we had imagined

1274
01:29:35,187 --> 01:29:36,104
Tara.

1275
01:29:37,896 --> 01:29:38,771
Tara.

1276
01:29:41,771 --> 01:29:42,729
Oh, God.

1277
01:30:19,812 --> 01:30:22,521
Everyone, please step out.

1278
01:30:22,604 --> 01:30:24,229
I think she needs rest.

1279
01:30:46,687 --> 01:30:47,687
Sorry, Dad.

1280
01:30:48,187 --> 01:30:49,062
Sorry?

1281
01:30:51,687 --> 01:30:53,604
Do you have any clue
what you are doing?

1282
01:30:56,479 --> 01:30:57,396
Any clue at all?

1283
01:30:58,021 --> 01:30:59,896
If Aman hadn't arrived on time,

1284
01:30:59,979 --> 01:31:01,396
do you have any clue
what could have happened?

1285
01:31:03,646 --> 01:31:05,729
-It won't happen again.
-Quiet.

1286
01:31:06,771 --> 01:31:07,729
Don't utter a single word!

1287
01:31:14,896 --> 01:31:17,562
I always stood up for you, child.

1288
01:31:18,312 --> 01:31:20,521
I sold everything I had in India
and came here for your sake.

1289
01:31:21,896 --> 01:31:23,687
I supported you. Fought for you.

1290
01:31:26,062 --> 01:31:26,937
And you…

1291
01:31:29,104 --> 01:31:30,646
You don't care about your own life.

1292
01:31:31,771 --> 01:31:33,229
I've had enough of your drama.

1293
01:31:33,771 --> 01:31:34,812
You are going nowhere.

1294
01:31:35,562 --> 01:31:36,396
Understood?

1295
01:31:36,479 --> 01:31:38,021
You're done scavenging the oceans.

1296
01:31:38,312 --> 01:31:39,187
Enough!

1297
01:31:48,312 --> 01:31:51,896
Your grandma has chosen
a suitor for you.

1298
01:31:53,562 --> 01:31:54,854
Take up the responsibility if you can.

1299
01:31:57,062 --> 01:31:58,646
Otherwise, you can just abide by it.

1300
01:31:59,104 --> 01:31:59,979
No.

1301
01:32:00,187 --> 01:32:01,062
What?

1302
01:32:02,854 --> 01:32:04,062
I don't want to get married.

1303
01:32:04,229 --> 01:32:05,229
Do you want to be alone then?

1304
01:32:05,812 --> 01:32:07,396
What did you get out of marriage?

1305
01:32:08,229 --> 01:32:10,604
Pain. Loneliness. Humiliation.

1306
01:32:11,146 --> 01:32:13,146
-Where is Mom?
-Don't cross your limits, Tara.

1307
01:32:15,146 --> 01:32:16,521
You don't know, Dad!

1308
01:32:16,812 --> 01:32:18,187
Mom betrayed you.

1309
01:32:19,937 --> 01:32:20,937
What did you do?!

1310
01:32:24,229 --> 01:32:25,146
What did you do?

1311
01:32:30,646 --> 01:32:31,604
Look, Tara.

1312
01:32:34,937 --> 01:32:35,812
If…

1313
01:32:38,187 --> 01:32:40,062
you can't do it, just tell me.

1314
01:32:42,104 --> 01:32:43,437
I will let go, as well.

1315
01:32:47,896 --> 01:32:49,729
Tara, I cannot handle this anymore.

1316
01:32:51,646 --> 01:32:52,937
I am sorry, Dad.

1317
01:32:53,979 --> 01:32:57,396
I will do as you say.

1318
01:32:58,146 --> 01:32:59,021
Tara.

1319
01:33:01,146 --> 01:33:02,646
I am tired.

1320
01:33:25,604 --> 01:33:27,521
I will never forget this favor, son.

1321
01:33:27,604 --> 01:33:29,021
Don't say that, uncle.

1322
01:33:30,146 --> 01:33:32,646
Tara isn't just my colleague,
she is also a good friend.

1323
01:33:32,729 --> 01:33:34,562
So, why don't you turn this friendship

1324
01:33:35,187 --> 01:33:36,729
into a relationship?

1325
01:33:36,896 --> 01:33:38,896
What are you saying?

1326
01:33:39,396 --> 01:33:40,812
Aman is a nice boy.

1327
01:33:41,479 --> 01:33:43,729
He likes Tara.

1328
01:33:44,104 --> 01:33:46,146
He even understands her job.

1329
01:33:46,354 --> 01:33:47,646
He's also from a good family.

1330
01:33:48,021 --> 01:33:49,854
He's a Sharma. Brahman.

1331
01:33:53,396 --> 01:33:59,021
Don't make a wrong decision
in a fit of rage.

1332
01:33:59,479 --> 01:34:03,229
The solution to your problem is right
in front of you.

1333
01:34:05,312 --> 01:34:08,604
Why take the pain of sending
your daughter to Mumbai?

1334
01:34:09,687 --> 01:34:11,604
On top of that,

1335
01:34:13,271 --> 01:34:15,854
if Tara and Aman accept my proposal,

1336
01:34:17,021 --> 01:34:19,979
then I will make them partners

1337
01:34:20,104 --> 01:34:21,229
in my company.

1338
01:34:22,979 --> 01:34:24,271
I've no children.

1339
01:34:25,062 --> 01:34:27,187
And life is unpredictable.

1340
01:34:29,146 --> 01:34:31,771
Someone will have
to look after Martin's Dredging.

1341
01:34:32,479 --> 01:34:34,021
Who better than these two?

1342
01:34:36,146 --> 01:34:37,271
Can the two of you handle it?

1343
01:34:38,729 --> 01:34:40,146
-I accept it.
-Good.

1344
01:34:41,062 --> 01:34:42,729
Let's ask Tara.

1345
01:34:42,854 --> 01:34:43,896
We do too.

1346
01:35:41,771 --> 01:35:42,646
Tara.

1347
01:35:43,604 --> 01:35:44,562
You!

1348
01:35:51,687 --> 01:35:53,396
What are you doing here?

1349
01:35:54,437 --> 01:35:55,771
I should be asking you this.

1350
01:35:57,396 --> 01:35:58,562
What are you doing, Tara?

1351
01:36:03,979 --> 01:36:05,229
Where were you, Neil?

1352
01:36:05,896 --> 01:36:06,854
Me?

1353
01:36:07,312 --> 01:36:08,646
You left without saying anything.

1354
01:36:10,146 --> 01:36:11,021
Let's leave.

1355
01:36:11,562 --> 01:36:12,562
I have a lot to tell you.

1356
01:36:12,896 --> 01:36:13,896
But first, let's get out of here.

1357
01:36:15,062 --> 01:36:16,021
Let's go.

1358
01:36:16,854 --> 01:36:17,729
Come.

1359
01:36:18,479 --> 01:36:19,479
I've so much to show you.

1360
01:36:30,604 --> 01:36:31,479
Come.

1361
01:36:34,396 --> 01:36:35,604
This will be our house.

1362
01:36:37,146 --> 01:36:39,312
This place will be
for your fish tanks.

1363
01:36:40,021 --> 01:36:41,062
You design the place.

1364
01:36:41,979 --> 01:36:42,854
How is it?

1365
01:36:43,646 --> 01:36:44,562
It's beautiful.

1366
01:36:45,771 --> 01:36:46,729
Baby!

1367
01:36:49,687 --> 01:36:50,687
I got the contract.

1368
01:36:51,229 --> 01:36:52,437
-Really?
-Yes.

1369
01:36:52,521 --> 01:36:54,229
Wow. I am so happy for you.

1370
01:36:54,437 --> 01:36:55,312
Thanks.

1371
01:37:05,979 --> 01:37:06,896
What happened?

1372
01:37:08,771 --> 01:37:09,729
I am sorry.

1373
01:37:12,937 --> 01:37:14,271
It's too late, Neil.

1374
01:37:25,396 --> 01:37:26,312
Tara.

1375
01:37:28,312 --> 01:37:29,312
Tara.

1376
01:37:32,396 --> 01:37:33,354
Ramesh.

1377
01:37:33,521 --> 01:37:34,646
-Hi. How are you?
-Hello.

1378
01:37:34,729 --> 01:37:36,021
-Excuse me, please.
-Go ahead.

1379
01:37:36,104 --> 01:37:37,062
What happened?

1380
01:37:39,646 --> 01:37:40,646
Where is Tara?

1381
01:37:41,604 --> 01:37:42,854
Tara must be in her room, Mom.

1382
01:37:42,937 --> 01:37:43,812
She isn't.

1383
01:37:45,062 --> 01:37:46,146
-Did you find her?
-No, Mom.

1384
01:37:47,396 --> 01:37:49,396
Good God. Did she run away?

1385
01:37:49,896 --> 01:37:51,937
