Memory for me?

1498
01:48:43,812 --> 01:48:44,854
Are you okay?

1499
01:48:49,187 --> 01:48:50,104
Tara.

1500
01:48:53,271 --> 01:48:54,146
What happened?

1501
01:48:57,146 --> 01:48:58,687
You killed my mother.

1502
01:48:59,562 --> 01:49:00,437
What?

1503
01:49:02,396 --> 01:49:03,604
Remember Sukanya?

1504
01:49:06,521 --> 01:49:07,771
Year 1992.

1505
01:49:07,979 --> 01:49:09,562
She went to Goa with her friends.

1506
01:49:09,771 --> 01:49:11,062
To look for George Harrison.

1507
01:49:14,979 --> 01:49:15,854
Look.

1508
01:49:20,937 --> 01:49:22,062
How would you remember?

1509
01:49:23,646 --> 01:49:25,396
Girls are just a toy for you.

1510
01:49:30,396 --> 01:49:32,396
My mom broke free by killing herself.

1511
01:49:35,312 --> 01:49:36,271
But Dad…

1512
01:49:37,896 --> 01:49:42,146
has been loving someone else's daughter
as his own for the last 30 years.

1513
01:49:43,396 --> 01:49:46,812
I am your curse
that's come down hard on my family.

1514
01:49:48,729 --> 01:49:50,604
Do you even remember who I am?

1515
01:49:59,979 --> 01:50:01,146
Tara Salgoankar.

1516
01:50:01,729 --> 01:50:04,604
Year 2012. Calangute Beach.

1517
01:50:05,562 --> 01:50:07,479
You came there with your friends.

1518
01:50:08,271 --> 01:50:09,271
You knew.

1519
01:50:10,021 --> 01:50:11,854
I knew it the moment I saw you.

1520
01:50:15,521 --> 01:50:16,896
You were skirting eyes.

1521
01:50:18,479 --> 01:50:19,479
I thought maybe…

1522
01:50:20,937 --> 01:50:22,646
you wanted to forget that moment.

1523
01:50:24,646 --> 01:50:25,687
So, I didn't mention it.

1524
01:50:27,729 --> 01:50:29,146
I don't forget faces, Tara.

1525
01:50:31,687 --> 01:50:32,729
And I can tell you…

1526
01:50:34,771 --> 01:50:35,729
that this face…

1527
01:50:38,354 --> 01:50:39,604
I've never seen it before.

1528
01:50:41,854 --> 01:50:42,896
You are lying!

1529
01:50:56,104 --> 01:50:58,146
Jazz Club, London. 1992.

1530
01:50:59,354 --> 01:51:01,146
I wasn't even in Goa at that time.

1531
01:51:02,396 --> 01:51:03,854
Your name is Kailash.

1532
01:51:22,271 --> 01:51:23,687
How is that possible?

1533
01:51:30,896 --> 01:51:32,979
Why did Mom commit suicide?

1534
01:51:39,021 --> 01:51:39,937
Tara…

1535
01:51:41,354 --> 01:51:42,354
I don't know why…

1536
01:51:43,854 --> 01:51:45,562
people run, not from their mistakes,

1537
01:51:46,604 --> 01:51:48,062
but the truth.

1538
01:51:50,521 --> 01:51:53,229
They dig a grave of lies
in their mind

1539
01:51:54,437 --> 01:51:56,521
to bury the truth.

1540
01:51:58,812 --> 01:52:04,854
And then that same
truth haunts them forever.

1541
01:52:07,562 --> 01:52:09,229
That's where lives are lost.

1542
01:52:13,771 --> 01:52:14,646
Maybe…

1543
01:52:15,729 --> 01:52:17,896
that's what your mother did.

1544
01:52:19,437 --> 01:52:20,771
It wasn't her fault.

1545
01:52:21,687 --> 01:52:23,646
Attraction isn't a sin,

1546
01:52:24,896 --> 01:52:26,104
neither is lust.

1547
01:52:28,604 --> 01:52:29,687
We are humans.

1548
01:52:30,937 --> 01:52:32,896
Illusions, delusions, lust…

1549
01:52:36,187 --> 01:52:37,562
It's a part of life.

1550
01:52:39,729 --> 01:52:41,104
You can't run from it.

1551
01:52:42,104 --> 01:52:43,479
We cannot escape from it.

1552
01:52:45,771 --> 01:52:47,479
Your mother made only one mistake.

1553
01:52:50,062 --> 01:52:52,604
She didn't think her
life partner was worthy

1554
01:52:53,812 --> 01:52:56,646
of sharing her pain with.

1555
01:53:02,687 --> 01:53:07,312
Tara, you have one such life partner.

1556
01:53:09,354 --> 01:53:10,229
Neil.

1557
01:53:12,146 --> 01:53:13,937
My life is just too messed up.

1558
01:53:17,104 --> 01:53:18,646
I am getting married to Aman.

1559
01:53:18,896 --> 01:53:20,271
He loves me a lot.

1560
01:53:20,896 --> 01:53:22,562
And I am pregnant with Neil's child.

1561
01:53:22,646 --> 01:53:24,271
I really love him a lot.

1562
01:53:27,396 --> 01:53:29,771
I don't know what to do.

1563
01:53:32,062 --> 01:53:33,062
Please help.

1564
01:53:33,646 --> 01:53:35,687
Can you tell me what to do?

1565
01:53:36,562 --> 01:53:38,062
Tara, when the time comes,

1566
01:53:39,979 --> 01:53:41,646
face the truth.

1567
01:53:43,646 --> 01:53:45,479
You don't need to run anymore, Tara.

1568
01:54:32,104 --> 01:54:35,021
Did you know
that starfish can heal itself?

1569
01:54:35,479 --> 01:54:39,062
It doesn't die even
if it's cut into pieces.

1570
01:54:39,646 --> 01:54:44,396
As for us, we are always caught
up in our past and future.

1571
01:54:45,187 --> 01:54:46,729
But life never stops.

1572
01:54:47,479 --> 01:54:50,479
You think we're caught
up in the wave of memories.

1573
01:54:51,021 --> 01:54:53,187
But life always finds its way.

1574
01:54:54,229 --> 01:54:55,521
As I have found my…

1575
01:54:56,479 --> 01:54:57,354
love.

1576
01:54:58,312 --> 01:55:00,021
Love heals every wound.

1577
01:55:00,312 --> 01:55:03,021
Love erases all that needs to be erased.

1578
01:55:03,396 --> 01:55:06,479
Love makes you live… again.

1579
01:55:07,437 --> 01:55:09,396
So don't be afraid to wander.

1580
01:55:10,021 --> 01:55:13,312
Because, in this sea of memories,
everyone needs to take a dip.

1581
01:55:14,271 --> 01:55:16,646
So don't be afraid of drowning.

1582
01:55:17,687 --> 01:55:20,729
Because life will take you ashore.
